Kana quiz — licensing boundary
==============================

This repository is distributed under two licences, split at one directory.

  Everything EXCEPT src/data/generated/   MIT                 — see LICENSE
  src/data/generated/                     CC BY-SA 4.0        — see
                                                                src/data/generated/LICENSE

The generated data is adapted from CC BY-SA dictionaries, so ShareAlike reaches
it. It does not reach the code: the code reads the data, it is not derived from
it, so the two are distributed as a collection rather than combined into an
adaptation, and CC BY-SA 4.0 does not require a collection apart from the work
itself to be licensed under its terms.

If you fork this: the boundary is the directory. Take the code under MIT. Take
the data under CC BY-SA 4.0, keeping the attribution in
src/data/generated/LICENSE, and note the Tatoeba carve-out recorded there.
